The United States has strongly condemned a recent terrorist attack in Abha, Saudi Arabia, which resulted in injuries to at least twelve innocent civilians. The Houthis have claimed responsibility for the attack, and the U.S. has pledged to work with Saudi Arabia and international partners to ensure those responsible are held accountable. President Trump has expressed his commitment to supporting Saudi Arabia in defending its people and territory from such attacks, reaffirming that the U.S. stands by its friends in the region.